text: Gunvor Eldegard (born 14 April 1963 in Årdal) is a Norwegian politician for the Labour Party. She was elected to the Norwegian Parliament from Akershus in 2005. On the local level Eldegard was a member of the executive committee of Ski municipal council from 1999 to 2003, and then served as mayor to 2005. ==References== * Category:1963 births Category:Living people Category:Members of the Storting Category:Labour Party (Norway) politicians Category:Mayors of places in Akershus Category:Women mayors of places in Norway Category:20th- century Norwegian women politicians Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians Category:21st-century Norwegian politicians Category:21st-century Norwegian women politicians Category:Women members of the Storting
